latestIgtvVideos.title: EFFORTLESS FASHION - CO-ORDS !!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
We’ve alll become lazy humans after the lockdown & have gotten used to staying super comfii in our PJs .. even though we want to wear our formal clothes, but we have nowhere to wear it to. We all want to shop, but don’t really need anything because we have nowhere to go again.. but then one thing that you definitely can spend on is co-ords!!
I’m a suckerrrr for co-ords! They are the most comfortable, effortless & yet super dressy outfits in my wardrobe🤩 These have been my airportt looks too until jan 2020 ( i’m crying internally 😭) .. but I really believe that spending on a co-ord is an long term investment, since you get two pieces that you can style separately as well as style them together. Every co-ord can atleast be worn in 6-7 different ways & i’d lovee to show you how. latestIgtvVideos.title: 2 white shirtss, 10+ ways to wear it!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
WHITE SHIRT is literally the most versatile piece of clothing in every wardrobe and can be worn in more than 18-20 completely different ways. I decided to do a few uncanny looks for the #Rewearwhiteshirt video! I took two white shirts,  one loose linen white shirt from my grandmom’s wardrobe (oversized shirt - you don’t need to spend on one, you can always steal it from another wardrobe) and took out one of my white shirts (that I haven’t worn for the longest of time), and styled them in some fancyyyy ways.. from casual to formal! There are alot of “white shirt styling” videos on the internet and i wanted to be a little different than belting oversized shirts or tying knots or just cropping it off! I hope you see the effort and like the video, even though it’s slightly longer than my other videos! See the entire video, it’s worth the 6 six minutes.. i promise!!
.

No one does better Polki & Jadau jewellery like Jaipur, so obviously had to go and find my dream bridal set there! 

Here are all the designers i checked out & loved (in descending order) :
1.) @ghatiwalajewellers - They were genuinely the best in terms of quality & making. The designs too were one of a kind and they’re open to customizing.

2.) @sunita_shekhawat_jaipur - Great designs. Great Quality. Gives expensive and is expensive 🤪
I did like the pieces but it didn’t match the girly vibe i wanted tbh. 

3.) @symetree.finejewels - The designs give maharani from the royals. Great making but felt they were a little overpriced for the quality but overall 9/10! They have a store in Mehrauli, Delhi too. 

4.) @raniwala1881 - No doubt they do great designs, Commercial to one of a kind. They have something for everyone. 8/10 quality but also something for every budget!

5.) @birdhichand - The designs on their instagram page are really good but somehow didn’t enjoy the collection at the store.. or maybe it wasn’t my type. The diamond sets infact were great, but i was looking majorly for Polki & Jadau.

6.) @thehouseoframbhajos - I walked in & walked out.. The pieces on the display seemed commercial and that’s not my vibe. Maybe if we explored a little could’ve found something. 

Missed going to @thegempalace because we were short on time.. 

Also, Most of them are open to customizing. So incase you’re a bride to be, save for later .. and incase you know of any other jewelers in Jaipur, drop in the comments below for a guide to brides!
